<body>
    <h1>Materials UI =E2=86=92 Federated GraphQL Migration Plan</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h1 id=3D"MaterialsUI=E2=86=92FederatedGraphQLMigrationPlan-Materia=
lsUI=E2=86=92FederatedGraphQLMigrationPlan">Materials UI =E2=86=92 Federate=
d GraphQL Migration Plan</h1>
<h2 id=3D"MaterialsUI=E2=86=92FederatedGraphQLMigrationPlan-JiraEpic&amp;St=
oryBreakdown">Jira Epic &amp; Story Breakdown</h2>
<blockquote>
 <p><strong>Scope</strong>: Cut over all materials UI pages in <code>pdex-u=
i-react</code> from <code>spark-graphql</code> monolith to the <code>plm-ma=
terials</code> federated GraphQL gateway. <strong>UI client</strong>: Apoll=
o <code>plmClient</code> (already exists in <code>network-library</code>). =
Switch per-query via <code>client: plmClient</code> prop. <strong>No codege=
n</strong> =E2=80=94 all TypeScript types are manual. <strong>Mutations</st=
rong>: Added to subgraph services (not a BFF layer). <strong>Cutover strate=
gy</strong>: Each domain is migrated in a single atomic PR =E2=80=94 no fea=
ture flags. Validate in dev/staging, ship the PR, revert if needed.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"MaterialsUI=E2=86=92FederatedGraphQLMigrationPlan-PhaseOrderingRa=
tionale">Phase Ordering Rationale</h2>
<p>Wash is the first domain to migrate because it has the lowest complexity=
, fewest ADR blockers, no saga mutations, and no Relationship service depen=
dency beyond the deferrable <code>teams</code> field. It proves the full en=
d-to-end migration pattern =E2=80=94 federated queries =E2=86=92 mutations =
=E2=86=92 legacy removal =E2=80=94 before tackling higher-complexity domain=
s.</p>
<p><strong>Key sequencing insight</strong>: All 8 concrete material types a=
lready exist as federated entities with <code>@key(fields: "id")</code> in =
<code>materials-hub</code>. The <code>material(id)</code> and <code>materia=
ls(ids)</code> queries work today and <code>__typename</code> routing is li=
ve. This means:</p>
<ul>
 <li>Cross-cutting <code>getMaterialByIdFromService</code> UI migration is =
<strong>Phase 0 infrastructure</strong>, not Phase 4.</li>
 <li>Hub (<code>BaseMaterial</code>) detail page and list/search have <stro=
ng>no dependency on other domain migrations</strong> =E2=80=94 they can be =
worked in Phase 2 in parallel with Color/Artwork/Trim/Fabric.</li>
 <li>Phase 4 is <strong>Search only</strong>.</li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
 <table class=3D"wrapped confluenceTable">
  <thead>
   <tr>
    <th class=3D"confluenceTh">Domain</th>
    <th class=3D"confluenceTh">Phase</th>
    <th class=3D"confluenceTh">ADR Blockers</th>
    <th class=3D"confluenceTh">Key Complexity</th>
   </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
   <tr>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Wash</strong></td>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd">1 =E2=9C=85 Start here</td>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd">ADR 0.1.9 (blocks <code>teams</code> field =
=E2=80=94 must resolve before Wash is complete)</td>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd">
     <p>3 small breaking changes</p>
     <p>Note: Whatever data dependency existed between Wash and Fabric in t=
he legacy `spark-graphql` monolith (likely shared resolver logic, shared lo=
aders, or shared context) is irrelevant once you're in federation. Each dom=
ain subgraph owns its own type and resolves independently. The `Wash` and `=
Fabric` entities are already live `@key` federated entities in `materials-h=
ub` =E2=80=94 they route independently via `__typename`.</p></td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Artwork</strong></td>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd">2</td>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd">ADR 0.1.3 (<code>bulkUpdateTeams</code>), AD=
R 0.1.7 (Relationship service), ADR 0.1.9 (teams)</td>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd">10 Colorway field deltas, linked artworks</t=
d>
   </tr>
   <tr>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Color</strong></td>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd">2</td>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd">ADR 0.1.3, ADR 0.1.9, Story 0.2.4 (<code>add=
Color</code> schema design)</td>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd">Archroma/Coloro/Pantone sub-types entirely a=
bsent</td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Trim</strong></td>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd">2</td>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd">ADR 0.1.3, ADR 0.1.9</td>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd">44 reference data queries, <code>approvedCol=
orRows</code> regression</td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Fabric</strong></td>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd">2</td>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd">ADR 0.1.3, ADR 0.1.9, ADR 0.1.6 (<code>rfidT=
agId</code>), ADR 0.1.7</td>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd">Clone sagas, costing breaking change, index-=
alignment bug</td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Hub (BaseMaterial)</strong></td>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd">2</td>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd">ADR 0.1.3, ADR 0.1.9, ADR 0.1.4, ADR 0.1.7</=
td>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd">Dynamic template system entirely absent (hie=
rarchy fetched at runtime =E2=80=94 unknown N types); Paper/Wood/UDM concre=
te sub-types absent; <code>composition</code> N+1 fan-out; <code>developedB=
aseMaterials</code>/<code>connectedBoms</code>/<code>searchResourceLinks</c=
ode> all two-hop via Relationship service (ADR 0.1.7); <code>createResource=
Link</code> cross-domain write-back (ADR 0.1.4); <code>suppliers</code> VMM=
 N+1; <code>validateMaterialUniqueness</code> needed for create flow</td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Palette</strong></td>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd">3</td>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd">ADR 0.1.3, ADR 0.1.5 (atomic mutations), ADR=
 0.1.9</td>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd"><code>relatedMaterials</code> semantic flip<=
/td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Combination</strong></td>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd">3</td>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd">ADR 0.1.3, ADR 0.1.6, ADR 0.1.8 (<code>isInt=
ernalUser</code>), ADR 0.1.9</td>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd">FSC complexity, 5-container branching</td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Search</strong></td>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd">4</td>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd">Story 0.2.5 (search shape design)</td>
    <td class=3D"confluenceTd">Cross-domain result rendering</td>
   </tr>
  </tbody>
 </table>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"MaterialsUI=E2=86=92FederatedGraphQLMigrationPlan-Phase0=E2=80=94=
Foundation&amp;ArchitectureDecisions">Phase 0 =E2=80=94 Foundation &amp; Ar=
chitecture Decisions</h2>
<blockquote>
 <p><strong>ADR dependency summary for all phases:</strong></p>
 <ul>
  <li>=E2=9C=85 <strong>ADR 0.1.1 (ACL/JWT)</strong> =E2=80=94 RESOLVED. Sp=
ring Security filter handles this automatically. No blocker.</li>
  <li>=E2=9C=85 <strong>ADR 0.1.2 (<code>getMaterialByIdFromService</code>)=
</strong> =E2=80=94 RESOLVED. <code>material(id)</code> / <code>materials(i=
ds)</code> on <code>materials-hub</code> works today =E2=80=94 all 8 concre=
te types are live <code>@key</code> entities. UI migration is tracked in Ep=
ic 0.2 (Story 0.2.6) as Phase 0 infrastructure.</li>
  <li><strong>:white_check_mark: ADR 0.10 (Material entity&nbsp;<code>teams=
</code>)</strong> =E2=80=94 Blocks <code>teams</code> read field on ALL 8 d=
omains. Domain services do not own team associations =E2=80=94 stored exter=
nally in the Relationship service. Resolve during Phase 1 so Phase 2 domain=
s are unblocked. <strong>Wash cannot be considered complete until this is r=
esolved</strong> (Story 1.1.5b), though the cutover PR can ship without the=
 <code>teams</code> field.</li>
  <li data-uuid=3D"6f212737-069a-4c07-9edd-a046dc54b50f"><strong>:white_che=
ck_mark:&nbsp; ADR 0.11 (Material entity b<code>usinessPartners</code> / <c=
ode>droppedPartnerIds</code>)</strong> =E2=80=94 Blocks <span style=3D"font=
-family: SFMono-Medium , SF Mono , Segoe UI Mono , Roboto Mono , Ubuntu Mon=
o , Menlo , Courier , monospace;">business partner and dropped business par=
tner fields on all materials domain entities.&nbsp; Currently resolved in i=
nternal GQL mono repo via access-control-service. <strong>Wash cannot be co=
nsidered complete until this is resolved</strong></span></li>
  <li>=F0=9F=94=B4 <strong>ADR 0.1.3 (<code>bulkUpdateTeams</code>)</strong=
> =E2=80=94 Blocks all domain <code>update{Type}Teams</code> mutation epics=
 in Phases 1=E2=80=933.</li>
  <li>=F0=9F=9F=A0 <strong>ADR 0.1.7 (Relationship service =E2=80=94 entity=
 links)</strong> =E2=80=94 Blocks Artwork linked artworks (Phase 2), Fabric=
 BOM/samples (Phase 2), Combination (Phase 3), Hub multi-hop (Phase 2).</li=
>
  <li>=F0=9F=9F=A0 <strong>ADR 0.1.4 (<code>createResourceLink</code>)</str=
ong> =E2=80=94 Blocks Fabric (Phase 2) and Combination (Phase 3).</li>
  <li>=F0=9F=9F=A0 <strong>ADR 0.1.6 (<code>rfidTagId</code>)</strong> =E2=
=80=94 Blocks Fabric <code>FabricSpecification.samples</code> (Phase 2) and=
 Combination FSC (Phase 3).</li>
  <li>=F0=9F=9F=A0 <strong>ADR 0.1.5 (Palette atomic mutations)</strong> =
=E2=80=94 Blocks Palette (Phase 3).</li>
  <li>=F0=9F=9F=A0 <strong>ADR 0.1.8 (<code>isInternalUser</code>)</strong>=
 =E2=80=94 Blocks Combination (Phase 3).</li>
  <li><strong>Phase 1 (Wash) can start immediately</strong> after Phase 0 i=
nfrastructure. ADR 0.1.9 blocks the <code>teams</code> field but not the re=
st of the Wash migration =E2=80=94 resolve it during Phase 1 so Story 1.1.5=
b can land before Wash is marked done.</li>
 </ul>
</blockquote>
<h3 id=3D"MaterialsUI=E2=86=92FederatedGraphQLMigrationPlan-Epic0.1=E2=80=
=94ArchitectureDecisionRecords(ADRs)">Epic 0.1 =E2=80=94 Architecture Decis=
ion Records (ADRs)</h3>
<blockquote>
 <p>Decisions marked =E2=9C=85 RESOLVED require no story. Open decisions ea=
ch require an ADR + proof-of-concept before the domains that depend on them=
 can begin.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr>
<p><strong>Story 0.1.1 =E2=80=94 =E2=9C=85 RESOLVED: ACL / Permission JWT S=
trategy</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li><strong>Resolution</strong>: A Spring Security filter has already been=
 implemented in the <code>plm-materials</code> subgraphs. The filter automa=
tically fetches the ACL token on every inbound request =E2=80=94 no per-res=
olver <code>getUserPermissionsJWT</code> call needed. This is transparent t=
o the UI and to federation entity resolution.</li>
 <li><strong>Impact</strong>: No ACL-related blocker on any domain. All pha=
ses can proceed without any ACL setup story.</li>
 <li><strong>No story required.</strong></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<p><strong>Story 0.1.2 =E2=80=94 =E2=9C=85 RESOLVED: <code>getMaterialByIdF=
romService</code> Replacement</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li><strong>Resolution</strong>: The federated equivalent is confirmed: <c=
ode>material(id: ID!): Material</code> (single) and <code>materials(ids: [I=
D!]): [Material]</code> (bulk) on <code>materials-hub</code>. All 8 concret=
e types already exist as <code>@key</code> federated entities =E2=80=94 <co=
de>__typename</code> routing is live today. No architectural decision neede=
d.</li>
 <li><strong>Remaining work</strong>: Pure UI migration =E2=80=94 inventory=
 call sites, swap to <code>plmClient</code>, adapt for <code>id</code>/<cod=
e>description</code>/no <code>SPARK_</code> prefix, use <code>__typename</c=
ode> to branch per concrete type. This is Phase 0 infrastructure work, not =
Phase 4.</li>
 <li><strong>This work is tracked in Epic 0.2, Story 0.2.6.</strong></li>
 <li><strong>No ADR story required.</strong></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<p><strong>Story 0.1.3 =E2=80=94 ADR: <code>bulkUpdateTeams</code> Replacem=
ent</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li><strong>Problem</strong>: Single mutation updates teams across 6+ mate=
rial types. No cross-subgraph mutation exists in federation.</li>
 <li><strong>Options</strong>:=20
  <ul>
   <li>A) N type-specific mutations: <code>updateColorTeams</code>, <code>u=
pdateFabricTeams</code>, etc. (preferred =E2=80=94 each subgraph owns its d=
ata).</li>
   <li>B) Orchestration subgraph: a dedicated subgraph that fans out to eac=
h domain subgraph.</li>
  </ul></li>
 <li><strong>Acceptance Criteria</strong>:=20
  <ul>
   <li>ADR written selecting Option A.</li>
   <li>Each domain subgraph listed with its required <code>update{Type}Team=
s</code> mutation signature.</li>
   <li>UI call sites inventoried (grep for <code>bulkUpdateTeams</code>).</=
li>
   <li><code>teams</code> field gap tracked in each domain epic's backend s=
tory.</li>
  </ul></li>
 <li><strong>Blocks</strong>: All domain mutation epics in Phases 2=E2=80=
=934. <strong>Does NOT block Phase 1 (Wash)</strong> =E2=80=94 Wash <code>u=
pdateWashTeams</code> is a net-new mutation, not a replacement for <code>bu=
lkUpdateTeams</code>.</li>
 <li><strong>Estimate</strong>: 3 pts</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<p><strong>Story 0.1.4 =E2=80=94 ADR: <code>createResourceLink</code> Write=
-Back</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li><strong>Problem</strong>: <code>applyParentUpdateForNewResourceLink</c=
ode> in the legacy resolver performs a cross-service read-modify-write afte=
r creating a resource link. This cannot be expressed as a federation mutati=
on.</li>
 <li><strong>Proposed solution</strong>: Move write-back to service-to-serv=
ice call inside the Relationship service. The UI calls a single <code>creat=
eResourceLink</code> mutation; the backend handles the cascade.</li>
 <li><strong>Acceptance Criteria</strong>:=20
  <ul>
   <li>ADR written confirming backend-owned cascade.</li>
   <li>Relationship service team notified / story created in their backlog.=
</li>
   <li>UI call sites for <code>createResourceLink</code> inventoried.</li>
   <li>No UI change required beyond switching to <code>plmClient</code> for=
 the mutation.</li>
  </ul></li>
 <li><strong>Blocks</strong>: Fabric (Phase 2), Combination (Phase 3). <str=
ong>Does NOT block Phase 1 (Wash).</strong></li>
 <li><strong>Estimate</strong>: 3 pts</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<p><strong>Story 0.1.5 =E2=80=94 ADR: Palette <code>addMaterial</code> / <c=
ode>removeMaterial</code> Atomic Mutations</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li><strong>Problem</strong>: Legacy Palette resolver does read-modify-wri=
te set arithmetic on <code>relatedMaterials</code>. Race condition exists. =
Federation cannot replicate this pattern.</li>
 <li><strong>Proposed solution</strong>: <code>spark-palette-service</code>=
 adds dedicated <code>addMaterialToPalette</code> and <code>removeMaterialF=
romPalette</code> mutations with atomic backend semantics.</li>
 <li><strong>Acceptance Criteria</strong>:=20
  <ul>
   <li>ADR written.</li>
   <li>Palette service team has stories for both mutations.</li>
   <li>Input/return types defined (suggest returning updated <code>Palette<=
/code>).</li>
   <li>Phase 3 Palette epic references this ADR.</li>
  </ul></li>
 <li><strong>Blocks</strong>: Palette (Phase 3). <strong>Does NOT block Pha=
ses 1 or 2.</strong></li>
 <li><strong>Estimate</strong>: 2 pts</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<p><strong>Story 0.1.6 =E2=80=94 ADR: <code>rfidTagId</code> Gap in <code>F=
abricSpecCombo.samples</code></strong></p>
<ul>
 <li><strong>Problem</strong>: <code>rfidTagId</code> exists in Elastic sea=
rch results but not in the <code>SampleV2</code> service data model. <code>=
FabricSpecCombo.samples</code> stitches both sources.</li>
 <li><strong>Options</strong>:=20
  <ul>
   <li>A) Add <code>rfidTagId</code> to the Sample subgraph data model (req=
uires SampleV2 service change).</li>
   <li>B) Sample subgraph contributes <code>rfidTagId</code> via <code>@pro=
vides</code> from the Search subgraph.</li>
  </ul></li>
 <li><strong>Acceptance Criteria</strong>:=20
  <ul>
   <li>ADR written with chosen option.</li>
   <li>If Option A: SampleV2 team has a story to add the field.</li>
   <li>If Option B: <code>spark-elastic-search-hub</code> schema updated wi=
th <code>@provides</code> directive.</li>
   <li>Phase 2 Fabric and Phase 3 Combination FSC stories reference this AD=
R.</li>
  </ul></li>
 <li><strong>Blocks</strong>: Fabric <code>FabricSpecification.samples</cod=
e> (Phase 2), Combination FSC <code>samples</code> (Phase 3). <strong>Does =
NOT block Phase 1 (Wash).</strong></li>
 <li><strong>Estimate</strong>: 3 pts</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<p><strong>Story 0.1.7 =E2=80=94 ADR: Relationship Service =E2=80=94 Subgra=
ph vs. Internal</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li><strong>Problem</strong>: Multiple domain resolvers call the Relations=
hip service to resolve <code>connectedBoms</code>, <code>relatedBoms</code>=
, <code>samples</code>, <code>developedFabrics</code>, <code>colorLinks</co=
de>, <code>biDirectionalLinkedArtworks</code>, etc.</li>
 <li><strong>Options</strong>:=20
  <ul>
   <li>A) Relationship service becomes a federation subgraph (BOM, Sample t=
ypes with <code>@key</code>).</li>
   <li>B) Relationship service remains internal; each domain DGS subgraph c=
alls it directly as service-to-service.</li>
  </ul></li>
 <li><strong>Recommendation</strong>: Option B =E2=80=94 internal implement=
ation detail; avoids exposing BOM/Sample as federated types prematurely.</l=
i>
 <li><strong>Acceptance Criteria</strong>:=20
  <ul>
   <li>ADR written confirming Option B.</li>
   <li>Service-to-service call pattern documented (HTTP client config, auth=
, retry).</li>
   <li>Each affected domain epic's backend stories reference this pattern.<=
/li>
  </ul></li>
 <li><strong>Blocks</strong>: Artwork linked artworks (Phase 2), Fabric BOM=
/samples (Phase 2), Combination (Phase 3), Hub multi-hop traversal (Phase 2=
). <strong>Does NOT block Phase 1 (Wash).</strong></li>
 <li><strong>Estimate</strong>: 2 pts</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<p><strong>Story 0.1.8 =E2=80=94 ADR: <code>isInternalUser</code> Proxy JWT=
 in Combination</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li><strong>Problem</strong>: <code>SPARK_Combination.js</code> branches o=
n <code>ctx.currentUser.internal</code> to generate different query shapes =
and calls an ACL proxy endpoint for internal user impersonation.</li>
 <li><strong>Acceptance Criteria</strong>:=20
  <ul>
   <li>ADR written confirming proxy JWT endpoint remains accessible from <c=
ode>spark-combination</code> DGS subgraph.</li>
   <li><code>ctx.currentUser.internal</code> equivalent confirmed available=
 in DGS request context.</li>
   <li>Combination subgraph design doc shows how the 5 container query shap=
es are preserved.</li>
  </ul></li>
 <li><strong>Blocks</strong>: Combination (Phase 3). <strong>Does NOT block=
 Phases 1 or 2.</strong></li>
 <li><strong>Estimate</strong>: 3 pts</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<p><strong>Story 0.1.9 =E2=80=94 ADR: Material Entity <code>teams</code> / =
<code>businessPartners</code> / <code>droppedPartnerIds</code> via Relation=
ship Service</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>
  <p><strong>Problem</strong>: In the legacy monolith, <code>teams</code>, =
<code>businessPartners</code>, and <code>droppedPartnerIds</code> on every =
material type are resolved via <code>commonResolvers/Teams.js</code> =E2=80=
=94 a shared utility that makes two hops:</p>
  <ol>
   <li><code>GET ${RELATIONSHIP_ENDPOINT}/{materialId}?resourceType=3Dteam<=
/code> =E2=86=92 returns a list of team node IDs</li>
   <li>For each node ID: <code>GET ${USERPROFILE_ENDPOINT}/teams/{id}</code=
> =E2=86=92 hydrates full <code>TeamV2</code> object</li>
  </ol>
  <p>The domain services (Wash, Color, Fabric, etc.) <strong>do not own tea=
m associations at all</strong> =E2=80=94 they are stored entirely in the ex=
ternal Relationship service. All 8 material types share this pattern via th=
e same <code>loadTeams</code> / <code>loadBusinessPartners</code> / <code>l=
oadDroppedBusinessPartners</code> utility. These fields are currently absen=
t from every federated subgraph schema.</p></li>
 <li>
  <p><strong>Options</strong>:</p>
  <ul>
   <li><strong>A) Each domain subgraph resolves teams independently</strong=
>: Each DGS subgraph (<code>spark-wash</code>, <code>spark-color</code>, et=
c.) adds a REST client for the Relationship service and duplicates the two-=
hop resolver logic. Simple to implement per-domain but duplicates the same =
code N times.</li>
   <li><strong>B) Dedicated <code>relationship-hub</code> subgraph extends =
all material types</strong>: A new <code>relationship-hub</code> subgraph p=
articipates in the <code>plm-materials</code> federation gateway. It uses <=
code>@key</code> to extend each material type (<code>Wash</code>, <code>Col=
or</code>, <code>Artwork</code>, <code>Trim</code>, <code>Fabric</code>, <c=
ode>Palette</code>, <code>Combination</code>, <code>BaseMaterial</code>) wi=
th <code>teams</code>, <code>businessPartners</code>, and <code>droppedPart=
nerIds</code> fields. One place to maintain; mirrors the existing cross-cut=
ting <code>commonResolvers/Teams.js</code> pattern exactly.</li>
   <li><strong>C) <code>materials-hub</code> subgraph owns cross-cutting fi=
eld resolution</strong>: Centralizes in an existing subgraph but conflates =
hub concerns with relationship concerns.</li>
  </ul></li>
 <li>
  <p><strong>Recommendation</strong>: <strong>Option B</strong> =E2=80=94 <=
code>relationship-hub</code> subgraph with federated <code>@extends</code> =
on each material type. This is the cleanest mapping of the existing cross-c=
utting pattern into federation and avoids duplicating resolver logic across=
 8 subgraphs.</p></li>
 <li>
  <p><strong>Acceptance Criteria</strong>:</p>
  <ul>
   <li>ADR written selecting preferred option.</li>
   <li>If Option B: <code>relationship-hub</code> subgraph scaffolded in <c=
ode>plm-materials</code>; <code>@key</code> entity stubs defined for all 8 =
material types; <code>teams</code>, <code>businessPartners</code>, <code>dr=
oppedPartnerIds</code> field resolvers implemented and tested.</li>
   <li>If Option A: each domain subgraph's backend story updated to include=
 the Relationship service REST client and two-hop resolver.</li>
   <li><code>TeamV2</code> type defined in the gateway schema (currently ab=
sent from all federated schemas).</li>
   <li><code>BusinessPartner</code> type defined (currently absent).</li>
   <li>Auth pattern for Relationship service calls from DGS confirmed (serv=
ice-to-service token or pass-through).</li>
   <li>All 8 domain backend stories updated to reference this ADR for their=
 <code>teams</code> / <code>businessPartners</code> / <code>droppedPartnerI=
ds</code> field stories.</li>
  </ul></li>
 <li>
  <p><strong>Blocks</strong>: <code>teams</code>, <code>businessPartners</c=
ode>, <code>droppedPartnerIds</code> read fields on ALL 8 domains across Ph=
ases 1=E2=80=934. <strong>Phase 1 (Wash) can ship without these fields</str=
ong> =E2=80=94 they can be deferred to a follow-up story (Story 1.1.5b) onc=
e this ADR is resolved, since the Wash detail page does not require team di=
splay to be functional.</p></li>
 <li>
  <p><strong>Estimate</strong>: 5 pts</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"MaterialsUI=E2=86=92FederatedGraphQLMigrationPlan-Epic0.2=E2=80=
=94Infrastructure&amp;DeveloperFoundation">Epic 0.2 =E2=80=94 Infrastructur=
e &amp; Developer Foundation</h3>
<ul>
 <li><strong>Problem</strong>: <code>plmClient</code> currently uses <code>=
new InMemoryCache()</code> with no configuration. The legacy <code>internal=
Client</code> has <code>dataIdFromObject</code> keyed on <code>SPARK_*</cod=
e> type prefixes and <code>humanId</code>. The federated schema drops <code=
>SPARK_*</code> prefixes and uses <code>id</code> (not <code>humanId</code>=
) as the canonical key.</li>
 <li><strong>Tasks</strong>:=20
  <ul>
   <li>Add <code>typePolicies</code> to <code>plmClient</code>'s <code>InMe=
moryCache</code> for all domain types: <code>Color</code>, <code>Artwork</c=
ode>, <code>Wash</code>, <code>Trim</code>, <code>Fabric</code>, <code>Fabr=
icSpecification</code>, <code>BaseMaterial</code>, <code>Palette</code>, <c=
ode>Combination</code>, <code>FabricSpecCombo</code>.</li>
   <li>Each type policy: <code>keyFields: ['id']</code>.</li>
   <li>Add <code>possibleTypes</code> for the <code>Material</code> interfa=
ce listing all concrete types.</li>
   <li>Add <code>possibleTypes</code> for <code>ArtworkOrColor</code> union=
 (used in Combination).</li>
   <li>Document that <code>__typename</code> checks in UI components must u=
se new type names (no <code>SPARK_</code> prefix).</li>
  </ul></li>
 <li><strong>Acceptance Criteria</strong>:=20
  <ul>
   <li><code>plmClient</code> cache correctly normalizes entities by <code>=
id</code>.</li>
   <li><code>Material</code> interface fragments resolve correctly in Apoll=
o cache.</li>
   <li>Unit test: cache write + read round-trip for each concrete type.</li=
>
  </ul></li>
 <li><strong>Required by</strong>: Phase 1 (Wash) and all subsequent phases=
.</li>
 <li><strong>Estimate</strong>: 5 pts</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<hr>
<p><strong>Story 0.2.3 =E2=80=94 Establish <code>*FederatedQueries.ts</code=
> File Convention</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li><strong>Problem</strong>: Each domain library currently has query file=
s (e.g., <code>colorQueries.ts</code>). We need a clear convention for addi=
ng federated query variants without breaking the legacy path.</li>
 <li><strong>Convention</strong>:=20
  <ul>
   <li>New file per domain: <code>washFederatedQueries.ts</code>, <code>col=
orFederatedQueries.ts</code>, etc.</li>
   <li>Each file exports: query documents (gql tagged), TypeScript types fo=
r request/response, and a note on which <code>plmClient</code> fields diffe=
r from legacy.</li>
   <li>Legacy query files remain untouched until the domain cutover PR is m=
erged.</li>
  </ul></li>
 <li><strong>Acceptance Criteria</strong>:=20
  <ul>
   <li>Convention documented in a <code>CONTRIBUTING.md</code> or inline co=
mment template.</li>
   <li>One example file created (<code>washFederatedQueries.ts</code>) as t=
he reference implementation (created as part of Phase 1 Wash migration).</l=
i>
   <li>PR template updated to remind engineers to add federated query file =
when migrating a domain.</li>
  </ul></li>
 <li><strong>Required by</strong>: Phase 1 (Wash) and all subsequent phases=
.</li>
 <li><strong>Estimate</strong>: 2 pts</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<p><strong>Story 0.2.4 =E2=80=94 Design: <code>addColor(providerType:)</cod=
e> Consolidated Mutation Schema</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li><strong>Problem</strong>: Legacy <code>addColor</code> mutation accept=
s a <code>providerType</code> discriminator to route to Archroma, Coloro, o=
r Pantone sub-flows. The federated <code>spark-color</code> schema has no m=
utations and no sub-type schema.</li>
 <li><strong>Tasks</strong>:=20
  <ul>
   <li>Design the federated mutation schema for color creation covering all=
 3 provider types.</li>
   <li>Options: single <code>createColor(input: CreateColorInput!)</code> w=
ith <code>providerType</code> enum, or 3 separate mutations.</li>
   <li>Define all required input types and confirm with <code>spark-color</=
code> service team.</li>
  </ul></li>
 <li><strong>Acceptance Criteria</strong>:=20
  <ul>
   <li>Schema design doc written and agreed with backend team.</li>
   <li>Input types fully specified.</li>
   <li><code>spark-color</code> team has a story to implement the schema + =
resolvers.</li>
   <li>Phase 2 Color mutation stories reference this design.</li>
  </ul></li>
 <li><strong>Blocks</strong>: Phase 2 Color mutations only. <strong>Does NO=
T block Phase 1 (Wash).</strong></li>
 <li><strong>Estimate</strong>: 3 pts</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<p><strong>Story 0.2.5 =E2=80=94 Design: <code>MaterialsList.tsx</code> Sea=
rch Shape (Flat vs. Interface + Fragments)</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li><strong>Problem</strong>: <code>MaterialsList.tsx</code> renders searc=
h results across all material types. The UI must decide: flat common-field =
query, or <code>... on Color { }</code> / <code>... on Fabric { }</code> in=
line fragments per type.</li>
 <li><strong>Options</strong>:=20
  <ul>
   <li>A) Flat: query only <code>Material</code> interface fields (<code>id=
</code>, <code>description</code>, <code>tags</code>, <code>primaryAttachme=
nt</code>, <code>designCycles</code>). Simpler, works today.</li>
   <li>B) Interface + fragments: query type-specific fields per concrete ty=
pe. More powerful but requires all concrete types in the federated schema.<=
/li>
  </ul></li>
 <li><strong>Acceptance Criteria</strong>:=20
  <ul>
   <li>Design decision made and documented.</li>
   <li>If Option B: list of per-type fields needed in the search result car=
d for each domain.</li>
   <li>Phase 4 Search stories reference this decision.</li>
  </ul></li>
 <li><strong>Blocks</strong>: Phase 4 Search UI only. <strong>Does NOT bloc=
k Phases 1=E2=80=933.</strong></li>
 <li><strong>Estimate</strong>: 2 pts</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<p><strong>Story 0.2.6 =E2=80=94 Migrate <code>getMaterialByIdFromService</=
code> UI Call Sites to <code>material(id)</code> Query</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li><strong>Why Phase 0</strong>: <code>material(id)</code> and <code>mate=
rials(ids)</code> work today =E2=80=94 all 8 concrete types are live <code>=
@key</code> federated entities with <code>__typename</code> routing. This i=
s pure UI plumbing with zero backend dependencies.</li>
 <li><strong>Inventory</strong>: All call sites in <code>pdex-ui-react</cod=
e> that use <code>getMaterialById</code> / <code>getMaterialByIdFromService=
</code>.</li>
 <li><strong>Tasks</strong>: For each call site, replace with <code>materia=
l(id: ID!): Material</code> or <code>materials(ids)</code> on <code>plmClie=
nt</code>. Use <code>__typename</code> to branch rendering per concrete typ=
e. Adapt for <code>id</code> (not <code>humanId</code>), <code>description<=
/code> (not <code>name</code>), no <code>SPARK_</code> prefix.</li>
 <li><strong>Acceptance Criteria</strong>: All call sites migrated. No rema=
ining calls to legacy polymorphic router.</li>
 <li><strong>Depends on</strong>: Story 0.2.1 (cache config).</li>
 <li><strong>Estimate</strong>: 8 pts</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<p><strong>Story 0.2.7 =E2=80=94 Migrate <code>bulkUpdateTeams</code> UI Ca=
ll Sites to Type-Specific Mutations</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li><strong>Why Phase 0</strong>: Inventory and wiring work is cross-cutti=
ng and should be planned upfront. Actual execution is gated on each domain'=
s <code>update{Type}Teams</code> mutation landing (Phase 2 domain epics), b=
ut the call site inventory and the UI-side switch can be tracked here.</li>
 <li><strong>Inventory</strong>: All call sites in <code>pdex-ui-react</cod=
e> that use <code>bulkUpdateTeams</code>.</li>
 <li><strong>Tasks</strong>: Replace each call with the appropriate type-sp=
ecific mutation (<code>updateColorTeams</code>, <code>updateFabricTeams</co=
de>, etc.). Each domain mutation is implemented in its subgraph (tracked in=
 Phase 2 domain epics).</li>
 <li><strong>Depends on</strong>: ADR 0.1.3, all Phase 2 domain <code>updat=
e{Type}Teams</code> mutations.</li>
 <li><strong>Estimate</strong>: 5 pts</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<p><strong>Story 0.2.8 =E2=80=94 Migrate <code>createResourceLink</code> UI=
 Call Sites</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li><strong>Why Phase 0</strong>: Cross-cutting call site inventory. Execu=
tion gated on ADR 0.1.4.</li>
 <li><strong>Inventory</strong>: All call sites in <code>pdex-ui-react</cod=
e> that use <code>createResourceLink</code>.</li>
 <li><strong>Tasks</strong>: Replace with federated <code>createResourceLin=
k</code> mutation on <code>plmClient</code>. Backend handles cascade (per A=
DR 0.1.4).</li>
 <li><strong>Depends on</strong>: ADR 0.1.4.</li>
 <li><strong>Estimate</strong>: 3 pts</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<blockquote>
 <p><strong>ADR dependencies</strong>: ADR 0.1.9 blocks the <code>teams</co=
de> / <code>businessPartners</code> / <code>droppedPartnerIds</code> fields=
 on <code>Wash</code> and must be resolved before Wash can be considered co=
mplete. All other Wash stories are unblocked and can begin as soon as Phase=
 0 infrastructure (0.2.1=E2=80=930.2.3) is done.</p>
 <p><strong>ADR 0.1.9 strategy for Phase 1</strong>: Ship the Wash cutover =
PR without the <code>teams</code> field. Resolve ADR 0.1.9 in parallel duri=
ng Phase 1. Deliver Story 1.1.5b (teams field) as a follow-up PR before clo=
sing the Wash epic. Wash is <strong>not done</strong> until 1.1.5b lands.</=
p>
 <p><strong>Why first</strong>: Lowest complexity domain. Single flat type,=
 no sub-types, no saga mutations, no Relationship service dependency beyond=
 the <code>teams</code> field. Proves the full end-to-end migration pattern=
 for all subsequent phases.</p>
</blockquote>
<h3 id=3D"MaterialsUI=E2=86=92FederatedGraphQLMigrationPlan-Epic1.1=E2=80=
=94WashBackendGap-Fill">Epic 1.1 =E2=80=94 Wash Backend Gap-Fill</h3>
<blockquote>
 <p>All stories in this epic are <strong>backend</strong> (<code>spark-wash=
</code> DGS subgraph in <code>plm-materials</code>). No ADR dependencies. C=
an start immediately.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Story 1.1.1 =E2=80=94 Resolve <code>washType</code> Non-Null Bre=
aking Change</strong></p>
