<h3 id=3D"MaterialsUI=E2=86=92FederatedGraphQLMigrationPlan-Epic2.9=E2=80=
=94Hub(BaseMaterial)BackendGap-Fill">Epic 2.9 =E2=80=94 Hub (BaseMaterial) =
Backend Gap-Fill</h3>
<blockquote>
 <p><strong>Why Phase 2</strong>: All 8 concrete types are already live <co=
de>@key</code> federated entities. <code>BaseMaterial</code> schema is well=
-populated today. No dependency on other domain migrations =E2=80=94 Hub ca=
n be worked in parallel with Color/Artwork/Trim/Fabric.</p>
 <p><strong>ADR dependencies</strong>: ADR 0.1.3 (teams mutation), ADR 0.1.=
9 (teams read field), ADR 0.1.7 (multi-hop Relationship service traversals)=
, ADR 0.1.4 (<code>createResourceLink</code> cross-domain write-back).</p>
 <p><strong>Key complexities confirmed from <code>SPARK_MaterialHub.js</cod=
e> and <code>spark-materials-hub-graphql</code></strong>:</p>
 <ol>
  <li><strong>Dynamic template system entirely absent</strong> =E2=80=94 <c=
ode>getMaterialTemplate</code>, <code>getMaterialTemplateHierarchy</code>, =
<code>getMaterialTemplateTypes</code>, <code>addMaterialTemplate</code>, <c=
ode>updateMaterialTemplate</code> all missing from federated schema. The te=
mplate hierarchy is fetched at runtime from <code>${endpoint}/templates/hie=
rarchy</code> =E2=80=94 there is no hardcoded list of types. This system dr=
ives all UDF attribute rendering and is required for create/edit flows.</li=
>
  <li><strong>Paper / Wood / UserDefinedMaterial concrete sub-types absent<=
/strong> =E2=80=94 each has its own queries (<code>GET_PAPER_BY_ID</code>, =
<code>GET_WOOD_BY_ID</code>), mutations (<code>addPaper</code>, <code>updat=
ePaper</code>, <code>addWood</code>, <code>updateWood</code>), enum sets (<=
code>GET_PAPER_ENUMS</code>, <code>GET_WOOD_ENUMS</code>), and full UI page=
s (<code>PaperForm</code>, <code>WoodForm</code>, <code>UserDefinedMaterial=
View</code>, etc.). None exist in the federated schema.</li>
  <li><strong><code>composition</code> N+1 fan-out</strong> =E2=80=94 each =
composition item resolves <code>hubMaterial</code> (another <code>getHubMat=
erial</code> call) + <code>template</code> (another <code>getMaterialTempla=
teByMaterialId</code> call). Must be solved with DataLoader batching in the=
 Kotlin DGS resolver.</li>
  <li><strong><code>developedBaseMaterials</code> two-hop</strong> =E2=80=
=94 <code>relationship.findRelationships(id, { includeNodeTypes: ['material=
'] })</code> =E2=86=92 then <code>getHubMaterials(ids)</code>. Blocked by A=
DR 0.1.7.</li>
  <li><strong><code>connectedBoms</code> two-hop</strong> =E2=80=94 <code>r=
elationship.whereUsedSearch(id, { includeNodeTypes: ['bill_of_materials', '=
packaging_bom'] })</code> =E2=86=92 then <code>getBomByIds</code>. Blocked =
by ADR 0.1.7.</li>
  <li><strong><code>searchResourceLinks</code> cross-domain fan-out</strong=
> =E2=80=94 Relationship service lookup =E2=86=92 then fan-out to artwork/f=
abric/trim/material loaders per <code>filterType</code>. Blocked by ADR 0.1=
.7.</li>
  <li><strong><code>createResourceLink</code> cross-domain write-back</stro=
ng> =E2=80=94 after creating the link, the legacy resolver calls <code>appl=
yParentUpdateForNewResourceLink</code> which fetches the target material fr=
om its own domain service and updates its <code>parent</code> field. Blocke=
d by ADR 0.1.4.</li>
  <li><strong><code>suppliers</code> VMM N+1</strong> =E2=80=94 each suppli=
er resolves VMM business partner details via <code>ctx.loaders.vmm.getByID<=
/code>. Must be batched in Kotlin DGS.</li>
  <li><strong><code>validateMaterialUniqueness</code> / <code>bulkValidateM=
aterialUniqueness</code></strong> =E2=80=94 uniqueness check mutations requ=
ired for the create flow; absent from federated schema.</li>
  <li><strong><code>addPaper</code>/<code>addWood</code> post-create side e=
ffects</strong> =E2=80=94 after create: associate attachment teams + update=
 material teams (same two-step pattern as other domains but explicit in Hub=
 resolver).</li>
  <li><strong>Reference data queries</strong> =E2=80=94 <code>getHubCodedOp=
tions(type)</code>, <code>getHubUnitsOfMeasure</code>, <code>getHubMaterial=
Types</code>, <code>getMaterialTemplateTypes</code> =E2=80=94 all missing f=
rom federated schema.</li>
 </ol>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Story 2.9.1 =E2=80=94 Add <code>BaseMaterial</code> Core Fields =
and Reference Data Queries</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>Add missing reference data queries to <code>materials-hub</code> schem=
a:=20
  <ul>
   <li><code>getHubCodedOptions(type: String!): [CodeDescription]</code> (S=
tatus, Origin, Certification, VisualDescription, Brand, PaperSubtype, WoodS=
ubtype, etc.)</li>
   <li><code>getHubUnitsOfMeasure: [UnitOfMeasure]</code></li>
   <li><code>getHubMaterialTypes: [String]</code></li>
  </ul></li>
 <li>Add missing fields on <code>BaseMaterial</code>:=20
  <ul>
   <li><code>teams: [Team]</code>, <code>businessPartners: [BusinessPartner=
]</code> =E2=80=94 <strong>blocked by ADR 0.1.9</strong></li>
   <li><code>droppedPartnerIds: [String]</code> =E2=80=94 <strong>blocked b=
y ADR 0.1.9</strong></li>
   <li><code>supplierInfo: BaseMaterialSupplierInfo</code></li>
   <li><code>recycledContent: Boolean</code></li>
   <li><code>productType: String</code></li>
   <li><code>inspiration: Boolean</code></li>
  </ul></li>
 <li>Fix <code>BaseMaterialColorway.humanId</code> =E2=86=92 <code>id</code=
>.</li>
 <li>Fix <code>BaseMaterialComposition</code>: add <code>hubMaterial</code>=
, <code>template</code>, <code>countryOfOrigin</code>, <code>size</code>, <=
code>certifications</code> sub-fields (currently stripped in federated sche=
ma).</li>
 <li><strong>Depends on</strong>: ADR 0.1.9 (for <code>teams</code> / <code=
>businessPartners</code> fields).</li>
 <li><strong>Estimate</strong>: 8 pts</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Story 2.9.2 =E2=80=94 Add Paper / Wood / UserDefinedMaterial Con=
crete Sub-Types</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>Add <code>Paper</code> type with all sub-type fields: <code>subType</c=
ode>, <code>bleaching</code>, <code>coating</code>, <code>pulpType</code>, =
<code>lamination</code>, <code>paperGrade</code>, <code>paperboardGrade</co=
de>, <code>corrugateFluting</code>, <code>tissueGrade</code>, <code>dryingT=
ype</code>, <code>nonWoodFiberContent</code>.</li>
 <li>Add <code>Wood</code> type with sub-type fields: <code>subType</code>,=
 <code>species</code>, <code>finish</code>, <code>reclaimed</code>.</li>
 <li>Add <code>UserDefinedMaterial</code> type with <code>details</code> (U=
DF attribute map).</li>
 <li>Add <code>__resolveType</code> logic in <code>materials-hub</code> to =
route <code>BaseMaterial</code> =E2=86=92 <code>Paper</code> / <code>Wood</=
code> / <code>UserDefinedMaterial</code> based on <code>classification</cod=
e>.</li>
 <li>Add Paper/Wood-specific enum queries (see <code>GET_PAPER_ENUMS</code>=
, <code>GET_WOOD_ENUMS</code>).</li>
 <li><strong>Estimate</strong>: 13 pts</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Story 2.9.3 =E2=80=94 Add Material Template System to <code>mate=
rials-hub</code> Schema</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>Add queries: <code>getMaterialTemplate(name: ID!, inheritAttributes: B=
oolean): MaterialTemplate</code>, <code>getMaterialTemplateHierarchy: [Mate=
rialTemplate]</code>, <code>getMaterialTemplateTypes(statuses: [String]): [=
String]</code>.</li>
 <li>Add <code>MaterialTemplate</code> type with full attribute tree: <code=
>attributes</code>, <code>parentTemplate</code>, <code>permissions</code>, =
<code>suppliers</code>, <code>composition</code>, <code>origin</code>, <cod=
e>certification</code>, <code>galleryTaxonomyMapping</code>, <code>definedB=
aseAttributeConfigurations</code>.</li>
 <li>Add mutations: <code>addMaterialTemplate(template: MaterialTemplateInp=
ut!): MaterialTemplate</code>, <code>updateMaterialTemplate(template: Mater=
ialTemplateInput!): MaterialTemplate</code>.</li>
 <li><strong>Note</strong>: This is the largest single backend story =E2=80=
=94 the template system is the backbone of all Hub create/edit flows.</li>
 <li><strong>Estimate</strong>: 13 pts</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Story 2.9.4 =E2=80=94 Add Multi-Hop Traversal Fields (Relationsh=
ip Service)</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>Add <code>developedBaseMaterials: [BaseMaterial]</code> =E2=80=94 two-=
hop: Relationship <code>findRelationships</code> =E2=86=92 <code>getHubMate=
rials</code>.</li>
 <li>Add <code>connectedBoms: [Bom]</code> =E2=80=94 two-hop: Relationship =
<code>whereUsedSearch</code> =E2=86=92 <code>getBomByIds</code>.</li>
 <li>Add <code>searchResourceLinks(targetIds, sourceIds, filterType): Resou=
rceLinkSearch</code> query =E2=80=94 Relationship lookup + cross-domain fan=
-out.</li>
 <li><strong>Blocked by</strong>: ADR 0.1.7.</li>
 <li><strong>Estimate</strong>: 8 pts</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Story 2.9.5 =E2=80=94 Add <code>BaseMaterial</code> Mutations</s=
trong></p>
<ul>
 <li>Add mutations:=20
  <ul>
   <li><code>addPaper(material: PaperInput!): Paper</code>, <code>updatePap=
er(material: PaperInput!): Paper</code></li>
   <li><code>addWood(material: WoodInput!): Wood</code>, <code>updateWood(m=
aterial: WoodInput!): Wood</code></li>
   <li><code>partialUpdateHubMaterial(id: ID!, partialMaterial: HubMaterial=
PartialInput!): BaseMaterial</code></li>
   <li><code>updateTeams(id: ID!, teamsToUpdate: TeamsUpdateInput): Boolean=
</code> =E2=80=94 <strong>blocked by ADR 0.1.3</strong></li>
   <li><code>associateAttachmentTeams(parentId: ID!, files: [String]!, team=
sToUpdate: TeamsUpdateInput!, relatedResourceIds: [String]): Attachment</co=
de></li>
   <li><code>validateMaterialUniqueness(material: NewHubMaterialInput!, pag=
e: Int): UniquenessResult</code></li>
   <li><code>bulkValidateMaterialUniqueness(bulkValidateUniqueRequest: [Bul=
kValidateUniqueInput]!): [BulkUniquenessResult]</code></li>
   <li><code>createResourceLink(resourceLink: ResourceLinkInput!): Resource=
Link</code> + cross-domain write-back =E2=80=94 <strong>blocked by ADR 0.1.=
